Durban - Two people were arrested in a major drug bust operation in Harding, south of KwaZulu-Natal, on Wednesday. A team made up of the Directorate for Priority Crime Investigation (Hawks), Crime Intelligence and Port Shepstone’s TRT and K9 searched a farm where they found a clandestine drug manufacturing laboratory, said Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi, national spokesperson for the Hawks. “Various elements of the SAPS Forensic Unit are currently administering the crime scene where large quantities of narcotics that resembles Mandrax and paraphernalia are being processed,” Mulaudzi said. He said the extent and value of the drugs is yet to be determined pending ongoing investigations. He also said the operation comes in the wake of months of collaborative investigations. Bheki Cele, Minister of Police, General Khehla Sitole, National Police Commisioner and Lieutenant General Godfrey Lebeya, Hawks Head welcomed the arrest and discovery made by the team. “Drugs and substance abuse is a serious problem and we will find these so called factories and shut them one by one.  We will continue with the strengthening of the multidisciplinary approach in responding to crimes of this nature, and intensify our campaign by working together with our sister departments and relevant stakeholders in the fight against drug and substance abuse,” Cele said. Daily News